data.title: MGM Resorts' mixed earnings: 24 cents EPS (missed 40-cent target), revenue $4.25B (beat $4.23B exp), China sales up 17%. Vegas sales down 7%.
data.description: MGM Resorts International recently reported mixed third-quarter results, with adjusted earnings per share at 24 cents, falling short of analyst expectations of 40 cents. However, revenue of $4.25 billion exceeded estimates and marked a 2% increase from the previous year. MGM China saw significant growth with $1.1 billion in sales (a 17% increase) and record adjusted EBITDA. The Las Vegas unit, on the other hand, experienced a 7% decline in sales due to hotel room renovations. Despite these challenges, MGM stock dropped over 3% in the past five sessions and nearly 8% in the last month, pointing to potential trading opportunities spurred by the company's volatility. data.title: Zcash's price surged over 800%, hitting $373 and surpassing Monero in value. The market cap reached $6.2 billion, leading in privacy coins. Arthur Hayes predicts it could hit $10,000.
data.description: Zcash (ZEC) saw a significant surge of over 8% on Friday, reaching approximately $373 and achieving an eight-year high. This increase made it the most valuable privacy-focused cryptocurrency, surpassing Monero (XMR). The market capitalization of Zcash reached $6.2 billion, surpassing Monero and solidifying its position in the privacy coin sector. ZEC's price has risen by more than 45% in the last week and has recorded an increase of over 800% since early October. This growth is notable as the broader cryptocurrency market has been in a consolidation phase. Privacy coins like Zcash and Monero offer anonymity by obscuring sender, receiver, and transaction data, which Bitcoin (BTC) does not provide. With increasing regulatory scrutiny on blockchain transparency, investors are showing interest in tokens that maintain transaction privacy. The surge in Zcash's value was accelerated by predictions made by BitMEX co-founder Arthur Hayes, who suggested that Zcash could potentially rally to $10,000, referring to it as a significant rotation play in the market. ZEC's price climbed from $272 in response to this prediction.

data.title: Long term care workers at Bisset Court in Cole Harbour, NS vote 100% in favor of strike with CUPE 4970 due to understaffing.
data.description: In Cole Harbour, NS, long term care workers at Bisset Court, represented by CUPE 4970, have unanimously voted in favor of a strike mandate. All votes cast were in support of potential job action. The workers are advocating for fair wages and better recruitment and retention strategies to address understaffing problems in the sector. Trina Walker, President of CUPE 4970, highlighted the frequent short staffing issues, noting that it's a rare occurrence to have a fully staffed roster. The unanimous vote reflects the strong stance taken by workers in demanding improvements in their working conditions.
